# Project Rules

- This project is `ReportingETLService`, a .NET 10.0 ASP.NET Core Web API for importing and maintaining sales and inventory data for LiveNation.
- Build and evolve the API around clear domain boundaries, reliable imports, and maintainable persistence and integration code.
- The authoritative `swarmforge/` directory is always the version-controlled folder at the project root, as a sibling of folders such as `features/`, `src/`, and `.worktrees/`; it is never `.swarmforge/` and never a nested folder inside `.worktrees/`.
- Keep swarm state project-local under `.swarmforge/`, worktrees under `.worktrees/`, and helper scripts under `.worktrees/swarmtools/`.
- Prefer straightforward .NET project structure over custom runtime infrastructure unless the feature clearly requires it.
- Maintain clear role boundaries, reliable startup behavior, and explicit agent handoff mechanisms.
